state_template.actions:
## Available Actions (Only use the following actions. DO NOT use other actions)

1. VIEW_PROBLEM
   - Action: "VIEW_PROBLEM"
   - Parameters: {{ "problem_id": "<problem_id>" }}
   - Description: View detailed information about a specific problem
   - Returns: Problem title, description, and sample test cases

2. GET_HINT
   - Action: "GET_HINT"
   - Description: Get a hint for a problem (consumes tokens)
   - Hint Levels:
     0. Competition Strategy ({level_0_cost} tokens):        
        - NOTICE, you MUST give parameters as {{ "hint_level": 0 }}   
        - Then I will provide you with competitive programming strategy and tips, which includes debugging checklist and contest strategy        

     1. Problem Relevant Textbook Hint ({level_1_cost} tokens):
        - NOTICE, you MUST give parameters as {{ "problem_id": "<problem_id>", "hint_level": 1 }}
        - Then I will provide you with textbook content relevant to the problem_id you give, which explains theoretical concepts and knowledge

     2. Knowledge Relevant Textbook Hint ({level_2_cost} tokens):
        - NOTICE, you MUST give parameters as {{ "hint_knowledge": "<hint_knowledge>", "hint_level": 2 }}
        - Then I will provide you with textbook content relevant to the hint_knowledge you give, which explains theoretical concepts and knowledge

     3. Similar Problem Hint ({level_3_cost} tokens):
        - NOTICE, you MUST give parameters as {{ "problem_id": "<problem_id>", "hint_level": 3 }}
        - Then I will provide you with problems and solutions similar to the problem_id you give, which helps understand the problem type and basic approach

     4. Knowledge Example Problem Hint ({level_4_cost} tokens):
        - NOTICE, you MUST give parameters as {{ "problem_difficulty": "<difficulty_level>", "hint_knowledge": "<hint_knowledge>", "hint_level": 4 }}
        - Choose problem_difficulty from Bronze, Silver, Gold, Platinum, Advanced and give the hint_knowledge you want to look up. Then I will provide you with example problems and solutions related to the knowledge points and the difficulty_level.

3. SUBMIT_SOLUTION
   - Action: "SUBMIT_SOLUTION"
   - Parameters: {{
     "problem_id": "<problem_id>",
     "solution": "<your_code>",
     "language": "<cpp|java|python>"
   }}
   - Description: submission a solution for a problem (consumes tokens)
   - Token Cost:
     - Each submission consumes tokens based on the submission status
     - Cost varies depending on whether the solution is accepted or rejected
     - Default cost is 100 tokens if not specified in competition rules
   - Returns: Submission status, score, and test case results

4. TEST_CODE
   - Action: "TEST_CODE"
   - Parameters: {{
     "code": "<your_code>",
     "language": "<cpp|java|python>",
     "test_cases": [
       {{
         "input": "<input_data>",
         "expected_output": "<expected_output>"
       }}
     ],
     "time_limit_ms": <time_limit_optional>,
     "memory_limit_mb": <memory_limit_optional>
   }}
   - Description: Test your code with custom test cases (consumes tokens)
   - Token Cost: {test_cost} tokens per test request
   - Features:
     - Test code without affecting competition score
     - Use your own test cases to debug and verify solutions
     - Get detailed execution results including compilation errors, runtime errors, etc.
   - Returns: Test results, execution summary, and token usage

Please respond using the following JSON format:
```json
{{
  "action": "<action_name>",
  "parameters": {{
    // Fill in parameters according to the action type
  }}
}}
```

